  "title": "First law of thermo - adiabatic and isothermal",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows the graph of 2 curves in a coordinate plane. The horizontal axis is labeled volume, in cubic meters, and the values 0.00 through 0.25, in increments of 0.05, are indicated. The vertical axis is labeled Pressure, in 10 to the 4 power pascals, and the values 0.0 through 4.5, in increments of 0.5, are indicated. The curves are labeled Process 1, isothermal, and Process 2, adiabatic. Both curves start at the point with coordinates 0.10 comma 4.0 and move downward and to the right, where process 1 curve stays above process 2 curve. The process 1 curve ends at coordinates 0.20 comma 2.0, and the process 2 curve ends at coordinates 0.20 comma 1.3.\" src=\"/images/66c8e95334fcb8630b688e640af430bf.svg\"></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">An ideal gas in a container with a moveable piston can be taken through the two different thermodynamic processes shown in the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P V\"><math alttext=\"P V\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>PV</mi></math></span></span> diagram. Process <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> is an isothermal expansion and Process <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> is an adiabatic expansion. Which of the following correctly indicates which process would cause a greater change in the absolute value of the internal energy of the gas, and provides a valid justification?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i4",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Process <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>, because the absolute value of the work done on the gas is greater for Process <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> than for Process <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span></p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Process <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>, because energy is transferred to the gas by heating in Process <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> but not in Process <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span></p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Process <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, because the absolute value of the work done on the gas is greater for Process <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> than for Process <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span></p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Process <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, because negative work is done on the gas and no energy is transferred to the gas by heating</p>",
        "value": "i4"
      }
    ]
  },
